(4591, 4, '2014-10-07 15:33:33', '2014-10-07 15:33:33', '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][vc_column_text animate="none" delay="0"]Muay Thai Coach Ibere Reis has been with Team Link since 2009, where he has positively influenced his students and help them make healthy life changes.  Coach Reis writes about how he started training Muay Thai, his own major influences and his amazing journey from South America to the USA:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nToday, was a really good day, after a Muay Thai demo in a Kindergartenschool (thanks for Miss Michelle Andrews Robbins for the opportunity),I was having lunch and talking with Julian Nguyen about Muay  Thai, Istarted to talk about my coaches and how all of them make a hugeimpact and difference in my life.For who doesn’t know, my Muay Thai life experience I will try toexplain a little bit now and thank all of my coaches and mentorsthrough the years that made all the difference in me and in my life.When I was a kid I was never the tallest or the strongest one,actually I always felt weaker than most kids my age, and of coursealways had a bully and for many times I was the target of them, neverfelt that I could overcome it, I did so many sports but fights ormartial arts wasn''t in the list I was afraid because I always feltweak, I started to surf (that I love till today), play soccer,volleyball... but no fighting, to tell the truth I did a little whileof Hapkido but didn''t feel comfortable, didn''t feel right... All thishappened when I lived at the beach in Peruibe, Brazil, I had my sonIbere De Alcatara Reis, I was 18 when he was born, and I feltlike I needed to go back to the big city (Sao Paulo) to continue tostudy and work. I moved to Sao Paulo to start to work and go tocollege when I heard about Muay Thai and Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu. Istarted to train right away and fell in love with Muay Thai I saw thatis was the real deal and could help me a lot, but never thought thatwould be where I am today and today still is not the end.I started to train Muay Thai with Marcelo Paulista, a guy that movedback to Sao Paulo after living in Curitiba and trained with the bestBrazilian fighters at that time, he came from CHUTE BOXE MarceloPaulista, yes the same gym as Anderson Silva, Wanderley Silva, Shogunand others. Man this was great, tough and rough training, after amonth I started to train every day, after couple months twice a day, Iwas so amazed and I was getting really good, so that weak kid wasn''tme anymore, he signed me up to fight, my first fight was already atournament WAKO (World Association of Kickboxing organizations), I wasfreaking out and scared I was about to fight with guys that had muchmore experience than me, guys that were fighting for a long time,anyways I won my first fight breaking my opponents nose so he wasunable to continue, my second fight after a few minutes was with areally tough guy who was stronger than me, I was getting beat up inthe first round when Marcelo asked me: ---Does this guy hit strongerthan me?  So I realize, hell no, Marcelo is 40 pounds heavier, andhits me hard, this guy can be strong but I’ve had worse! Then Iknocked him down and I won the fight, I just lost the final I felt noenergy after all.Since this event I knew, that is what I want do to with My life, Iwant to do what he did for me, I was another guy already, confident,strong, it was life changing for me and from that day on I knew Iwanted to become a coach and change other people’s lives too!  Acouple months past, I still was focused on training but now, payingmore attention to how people move, what other fighters do, how they doit in every aspect of Muay Thai. I started to train at Never Shake,all professional fighters, huge team and great coaches, who had mindblowing talents. It was guided by Francisco Veras (THE KILLER, manhe really is the killer) and the Thai Master Pairojnoi Muay Thai,every day, every little sneak trick, every movement and hard work, allthe killer sparring, the conversations, the Muay Thai concepts, rules,mindset, skills, at that point I was addicted and absorbing it all,then Master Pairojnoi moved back to Thailand, Veras moved to VitoriaBrazil (if I remember correctly), and I was coaching already. I wastrying to save money to live in Thailand and train, but my son had todo some surgeries and I crashed my mom’s car, so there went all mymoney, I got a job in a company and needed do come to USA for a 3months for training in California, then back to Brazil again where Ihad the opportunity to work again with Marcelo but this time I wasthere to help him out cause he was about to fight for the BrazilianMuay Thai title and he won.   I wasn''t that motivated anymore, Iwasn''t fighting or coaching that often, I was helping a couple friendswhen they had fights but that was pretty much it when I talked withMarcio Onorato and he got meback on track, I was training and helping his fighters often, he madeall the change in that chapter of my life, great friends, greatenvironment, everybody helping each other, everyone winning theirfights, Marcio was more than a friend for me, he was a Coach, trainingpartner, friend and family that i was really needing, like I said hegot me back on track. A couple months after I was talking with GabrielGonzaga that invited me to help him out with training and to teach inhis gym in USA, after 2 weeks I was here past 5 years that I’m here inUSA and 12 years of train/coaching. In 2009 I started the Team LinkMuay Thai, I coached so many fighters from the small events to thehighest events ( from gyms smokers to UFC and Lion Fight Promotions),in MMA and Muay Thai ( Thank you Marco Alvan too, for trust in my workand for many opportunities that I had). Now Im so happy and proud ofit, so many lives Ive been able to change, so many guys that didn''tknow how to throw a punch or kick, became champions and are winningevery fight, after a year of training every day with me, Julian wonthe best technical performance on the Worlds in Thailand (thank youKru Mark Nardone that had done an incredible work with Julian beforeme and for being of the best real Muay Thai representative in USA).After all the years so many friends so many people so much change inmy life, I really want to thank all my coaches through the years, youguys Marcelo Paulista, Veras, Pairojnoi and Marcio Onorato are part ofall this, I didn''t do anything alone, I couldn’t do anything if wasn''tfor you guys, THANK YOU from the deepest part of my heart!  Here are afew pics through the years.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Coach Ibere Reis (Biography)', 'Muay Thai Coach Ibere Reis has been with Team Link since 2009, where he has positively influenced his students and help them make healthy life changes.  Coach Reis writes about how he started training Muay Thai, his own major influences and his amazing journey from South America to the USA', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'coach-ibere-reis-biography', '', '', '2015-02-16 02:11:23', '2015-02-16 02:11:23', '', 0, 'http://teamlinkmuaythai.dev/?p=4591', 0, 'post', '', 0),
